{"questionId":"11894","questionHtml":"<p>Find the Cartesian equation satisfied by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"u\">\n  <mi>u</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span> and state the geometric shape that this curve represents.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{X}{{\\sqrt 3 }} = u{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\frac{Y}{{\\sqrt 2 }} = v \\Rightarrow {u^2} + {v^2} = 1\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>X</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>u</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>Y</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>, a circle (centre at the origin radius of 1)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11894","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.5f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the Cartesian equation satisfied by u and v and state the geometric shape that this curve represents.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}